The JavaScript files contain basic UI interaction logic for dropdowns, radio buttons, and flash messages. These don't appear to handle sensitive data or perform operations that could lead to common web vulnerabilities like cross-site scripting (XSS) or injection attacks.

The HTML files are static error pages (404, 422, 500) which don't process user input or display dynamic content, minimizing attack surfaces.
